   "source": [
    "# Experiment\n",
    "\n",
    "One `@register_run`-decorated `run()` is the experiment. `hpc-agent`\n",
    "exports the importable surface of this notebook (imports, defs,\n",
    "classes, UPPERCASE constants) to a sibling `.py` executor; scratch\n",
    "cells — plots, smoke tests, exploratory assignments — are dropped.\n",
    "\n",
    "Run `make export` (or commit — the pre-commit hook does it) to keep\n",
    "the exported `.py` in sync."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from hpc_agent.incorporation.template import register_run"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "@register_run\n",
    "def run(alpha: float = 1.0) -> dict:\n",
    "    \"\"\"Return this experiment's metrics as a dict (results-by-return).\"\"\"\n",
    "    return {\"score\": alpha, \"n_samples\": 1}"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Scratch cell — dropped on export. Smoke-test the run here.\n",
